to create an dropdown list use the following, it can be added into a form but it's fine with out one.
(if using a form makesure to reminder to stop the default from running on submit "e.preventdefault")

<label>My Dropdown</label> // Create the label for
<select>
  <option>  Dropdown one </option>
  <option>  Dropdown one </option>
  // add your dropdown options , each requires it's own option
  
</select> // this creates the dropdown button

Each option also requires a "value" this value is what gets sent to the server when selected

div>
			<label for="superpowers">Choose Your Superpower:</label>
			<select id="superpowers">
				<option value="flight">Flight</option>
				<option value="Invisibility">Invisibility</option>
				<option value="superStrength">Super Strength</option>
				<option value="Telepathy">Telepathy</option>
				<option value="timeTravel">Time Travel</option>
				<option value="Wisdom">Wisdom</option>
			</select>
		</div>

If you want an element to be seleted by default use the "selected" attribute, this is simliar to required

mulitple attribute allows you to select multiple options

<optgroup> this splits out the grops if required, this nest the options under optgroup make sure to give a label to optgroup

Inserting icons or other items via a CDN eg CDNJS you can add icons to your HTML just copy the link and add this into the <head> of your HTML

DATA ATTRIBUTE
Linking things like icons to pictures and ensuring icons or anything else for that matter belong to that need to use the data attribute, the syntax is the following
data-myPictureData = "your Data".

To acess the dataattribute you can use the event eg document.addEventlistern(e) {
console.log(e.target.dataset.insertnamehere) This will look out the name you havd assiged it in the HTML

.parentElement will target all elements inside the main DIV good for using with event for targetting dynamic content.
.classlist use this to target specific CSS selectors to change the content using an if statement


